 application/test class loader, so the public constructor and provider registration path take the `ClassLoader#loadClass` branch instead of the fallback `Class#forName` branch owned by `BouncyCastlePQCProvider$2`.\n\nReaching the remaining site would require non-public or unsupported techniques such as:\n\n- putting the test in `org.bouncycastle.pqc.jcajce.provider`,\n- invoking the package-private `loadClass` method reflectively,\n- redefining/loading Bouncy Castle classes on the bootstrap classpath,\n- using instrumentation/Unsafe/custom JVM launch tricks,\n- or creating shadow/helper classes in the library package.\n\nThose would violate the task and repository rules requiring supported public API coverage, tests outside library packages, and no direct reflection unless naturally required by the public API.\n\nSo I left the call site uncovered rather than adding a misleading or rule-violating test.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_076c652cf70e021b016a269d1130d48196a35fc952a225fe70\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1408, "output": 814, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29870, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780915454214, "responseId": "resp_076c652cf70e021b016a269cfea6b0819699f1c369629a5214"}}
